Find Pivot Index(https://leetcode.com/problems/find-pivot-index/)
====================
class Solution {
    public int pivotIndex(int[] nums) {

        int totalSum = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            totalSum += num;
        }

        int leftSum = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {

            int rightSum = totalSum - leftSum - nums[i];

            if (leftSum == rightSum) {
                return i; // leftmost pivot index
            }

            leftSum += nums[i];
        }

        return -1;
    }
}
==========================================================================

Step 1: Find the total sum

Imagine adding all numbers together.

Example:

[1,7,3,6,5,6]
totalSum = 28

Step 2: Walk through the array

We keep track of:

leftSum â†’ sum of numbers before current index

rightSum â†’ everything else

Formula:

rightSum = totalSum - leftSum - currentNumber

Step 3: Check pivot condition

If:

leftSum == rightSum


ðŸŽ‰ That index is the pivot â†’ return it.

